-- Tanzania Granted German, European Union Funds for Water Projects
-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 2012-12-06T12:10:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-06/tanzania-granted-german-european-union-funds-for-water-projects.html
Tanzania will gain 71.3 million euros
($93 million) in funding from the European Union and Germany via
the KfW development bank for water and sewage projects in towns
including Kigoma and Lindi.  The EU-German statement handed to reporters in the
commercial capital of  Dar es Salaam  today said the sanitation
and water projects would also take place in the towns of
Sumbawanga, Mtwara and Babati.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Malingha Doya in Dar es Salaam at 
 dmalingha@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Randall Hackley at 
 rhackley@bloomberg.net  